Build a complete React + Vite frontend UI for a responsive web app called Easy Dine.

Easy Dine is a premium internal food ordering platform for Prodapt employees. It has 3 roles:
1. Employee/User
2. Vendor/Restaurant Staff
3. Admin

Use mock data only. No backend now. Use React Router. Build all pages fully with realistic mock data. No blank placeholder pages.

FINAL RESTAURANTS/SHOPS:
Use only these two names everywhere:
1. Meal Counter
2. Tuck Shop

IMPORTANT LOGIN FLOW:
Do NOT create a separate role selection page.
Create one unified login page at /login.
Inside the login page, add a role segmented control/tabs:
Employee | Vendor | Admin

After Sign In:
Employee -> /employee/mode-selection
Vendor -> /vendor/dashboard
Admin -> /admin/dashboard

Employee login uses Email + Password.
Vendor login uses Phone/Email + Password.
Admin login uses Email + Password.

GLOBAL UI STYLE:
Match the uploaded screenshots closely.
Premium red theme: #ff1c12.
Background: warm white / cream / very light gray.
Cards: white, 20px-28px rounded corners, soft shadows.
Buttons: red filled primary, white outlined secondary.
Typography: bold black titles, gray subtitles, clean hierarchy.
Inputs: rounded, light border, soft red focus.
Use ₹ for all prices.
Mobile-first polished app style.
Employee screens should feel like a native food ordering mobile app.
Vendor/Admin screens should feel like compact premium enterprise dashboards.
No old admin template UI.
No huge blank stat cards.
No clutter.
No unnecessary pages.
No kitchen statuses like Preparing or Ready.
Order statuses ONLY: Delivered and Rejected.

RESPONSIVE:
Mobile Employee: floating rounded bottom nav.
Mobile Vendor/Admin: top header + hamburger drawer.
Desktop Vendor/Admin: left sidebar.
Desktop Employee: centered premium layout, still responsive.
Use cards on mobile and compact grids/tables on desktop.

